<h1>Wildfire Burn Severity Mapping</h1>
<p><strong>Tools:</strong> ArcGIS Pro, Senintel-2 Imagery, Raster Algebra</p>

---

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
This project evaluates wildfire burn severity using differenced Normalized Burn
Ratio (dNBR) derived from pre- and post-fire Senintel-2 surface reflectance imagery.
The objective was to identify spatial patterns of burn severity across the fire
perimeter.
</p>

---

<h2>Data</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Senintel-2 Imagery (pre- and post-fire)</li>
  <li>Study area boundary</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>Methods</h2>
<ul>
<li>Calculated NBR using NIR () and SWIR () bands</li>
  <li>Computed dNBR with raster differencing</li>
  <li>Classified burn severity using published thresholds from National Forest Service</li>
</ul>

---

